caption.text: When i give up on a math problem, i ask Princess Kylie to solve it. Thank you, my Princess for your help, i meant it #littleprincess

*in the morning* (before going to church)
I'm sitting in front of the door with a cup of coffee next to me.
Lysa comes up and says,
"Are you alright, John?"
John : "Yeah, all good, lysa"
Lysa : "Are you sure?"
John : "I'm sure" (with smile on my face)
Lysa : "Are you gonna go to church?" (with a lovely british accent)
John : "Yup, after i finnish my coffee"
Lysa : "allright"
*After 3 minutes*
(Lysa opens the door and sits beside me)
Lysa : "tell me what happen?"
(I'm speechless in 5 seconds)
(Then I speak up)
John : "It's just about my marks, ... bla bla bla)
Lysa : *laughing* You're just a lazy boy. Look at yourself, you just waste your time with your friends, every single day. Honestly, you are a smart boy, John, but you just don't know it. I can see from how you act to other people, how you speak and also how the way you fix something when i need a hand, you see. You just haven't found your passion, the thing that make you happy, hunger, and concious to do and to try it over and over again. Just try to understand and ask me a question if you have, okay. We'll work this out together, because i know you can and you're a nice boy, hunny.
(with a lovely smile on her face and annoying british accent ‚úåÔ∏è)
Lysa : Okay, you better go now, otherwise you'll be late, John. ~~~
